HEADWORD: Bergschrund
<hw>Berg"schrund`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., lit.,
mountain gap.]</ety> <fld>(Phys. Geog.)</fld> <def>The crevasse or
series of crevasses, usually deep and often broad, frequently occurring
near the head of a mountain glacier, about where the n⟦eacute⟧v⟦eacute⟧
field joins the valley portion of the glacier.</def>⟦br⟧
